For me the big difference between dynamic and statically typed languages is catching bugs like:<p><pre><code>    foo = bar()
    if foo:
      fooo = baz()
</code></pre>
in a static language, you&#x27;d have to write int foo = and the third line where you have an assignment fooo would be caught by the compiler. Of course there&#x27;s advantages to dynamic languages, like being able to write something like<p><pre><code>    mydata = {}
    mydata[&#x27;foo&#x27;] = {}
    mydata[&#x27;foo&#x27;][&#x27;bar&#x27;] = MyObject()
</code></pre>
without a lot of boilerplate
